                                    <h4>What does it mean to create a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        If you want to offer a ride to other people,  who want to go to the same destination as you are, you can create a ride.
                                        People can then make a booking of your ride. 
                                        If you accept them, you will all drive to the destination together.

                                    </p>

                                    <h4>What will I earn when I create  and make a ride with passengers?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        Our application is fully without money. There is no exchange of money between the driver and the passengers.
                                        It means, no one will pay you for driving him or her.  You will also not recieve any payment for the ride. 
                                        Our Carpooling concept is mainly based on saving the environment from carbon emmissions 
                                        and giving the car poolers a platform where they can make new friends. 

                                    <h4>How to create a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To create a ride you need to be logged in and have at least one car created in your list of cars on your personal profile page.
                                        After these two conditions are successfully completed, click on the rides page.
                                        Here you can see "Add new ride"  button which will redirect you to the  form for filling all the necessary information.
                                        In case you decide not to create the ride, just click on the link "Back to My rides" at the end of the page.
                                        Otherwise, you should fill out all the required fields on this form.
                                        After you fill all of them, click on "Create" button and you are going
                                        to be redirected to "List of all rides" where your newly created ride is will be displayed.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Other way is to open your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the right side and 
                                        choose the "My Rides" option on the left side of the page.
                                        Here you can see the list of your Rides and also a button "Add New Ride" which will redirect you to the form for creating a ride.
                                        Then proceed the ride creation as mentioned above.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        In case you are still completely lost and have no idea how to access the form for creating a ride, 
                                        here is the link but don't forget to be logged in and have a car created!<br />
                                        <a asp-page="/Rides/CreateRide">Create a ride</a>
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Where can I see the list of my rides?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        You have to be logged in and have at least one ride created.
                                        Just open your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the right side.
                                        On this page you can see "My Rides" on the left side where the list of rides you created are displayed.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to edit a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To edit a ride, you have to be logged in and have at least one ride created.
                                        Go to your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the right side.
                                        Now on the left side choose the "My rides" option which shows the page with the list of all your created rides.
                                        Here in every line is a blue button with a pen inside for editing exactly that one ride.
                                        Click on that and to make sure you are editing the right ride. Fill in the information you want to edit and click "Save" button.
                                        This action will  move you back to the list of all rides where the information is  going to be changed immediately.
                                        If you find out you do not wish to edit this ride, just click on the link "Back To My Rides" which will take you back to the list of rides.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way to edit a ride is to open a page with Rides where you can see also your rides.
                                        Next to each your ride you can see the blue button with a pen inside for editing it.
                                        This button will take  you to the "Edit Page" for the ride.
                                        To make sure you are editing the right ride, all the information about it are provided.
                                        If you find out you do not wish to edit this one ride, just click on the link "Back To My Rides" which will move you back to the list of your rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to edit, change all the necessary information you need and click on "Save Changes" button.
                                        This action will  move you back to the list of all rides where the information are going to be changed immediately.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One other way is to either open "Rides" Page, choose the ride you want to edit and click on "Details" at the end of the line of the ride,
                                        or choose the ride from "My Rides" option in your personal profile page and  again, click on details in the end of the line of the ride which is supposed to be changed.
                                        Both links will move you to detailed page of your ride where on the bottom of the page you can see again button for Editing Ride.
                                        To make sure you are editing the right ride, all the information about it is provided.
                                        If you find out you do not wish to edit this  ride, just click on the link "Back To Rides" which will take you back to the list of rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to edit, change all the necessary information you need and click on "Save Changes"  button.
                                        This action will take you back to the list of all rides where the information is going to be changed immediately.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to cancel or delete a ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        To cancel a ride, you have to be logged in and have at least one ride created.
                                        Go to your personal profile page by clicking on your name up on the right side.
                                        Now on the left side choose the My rides option which shows the page with all your created rides.
                                        Each ride has on the right side of lines the red button with trash can inside for cancelling.
                                        After clicking on it you are going to be redirected to the page which asks you if you are really sure you want to delete the ride.
                                        Make sure you chose the right one by checking all the information on the current page and confirm it by clicking on "Delete"  button.
                                        The ride will be immediately deleted and not displayed to others anymore.
                                        In case you find out you do not wish to delete exactly this one ride, 
                                        click on "Back to My Rides" link on the bottom of page and it will take you back to the list of your rides where you can choose the right ride.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way to delete a ride is to open a page with "Rides" where you can see also your rides.
                                        Next to each your ride you can see the red button with a trash icon  for deleting it.
                                        This link will move you to the "Delete" Page for the ride.
                                        To make sure you are deleting the right one, all the information about this ride is displayed.
                                        If you find out you do not wish to delete this one ride, just click on the link "Back To My rides" which will take you back to the list of rides.
                                        If you are sure this one is the ride you want to delete click on "Delete"  button.
                                        This action will  take  you back to the list of rides where the ride is not shown anymore.

                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One more way is to either open "Rides" Page.
                                        Choose the ride you want to delete.
                                        Click on "Details" at  the end of the line of the ride.
                                        Or, choose the ride from "My Rides" option in your personal profile page.
                                        Click on "details" at the end of the line of the ride which is supposed to be changed.
                                        Both links will take  you to "details" page of your ride where at the bottom of the page you can see the button for Deleting Ride.
                                        To make sure you are deleting the right one, all the information about this ride is deleted.
                                        Click on the "Delete ride" button displayed on the screen and the ride will be deleted immediately.

                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>!!!When a ride is deleted, all its corresponding bookings are also deleted. !!!</b>
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Can I cancel the ride even if someone has booked it?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        Yes, you can cancel a ride anytime before it happens. The cancellation is free.
                                        So even if someone has booked your ride, you can still cancel it.
                                        You can find more information about how to do so in the previous question.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How do I know if someone has booked my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        After another user books your ride, you will get a notification and also a message. 
                                        All your notifications can be found under the bell next to your name up on the right side.
                                        Next to the notification bell, there are messages.
                                        Any new messages are reflected with a red  circle around the message icon i.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another place where you can find out if someone has booked your ride is on your personal profile page.
                                        There when you choose the "My Rides" option on the left side, the list of your rides is displayed.
                                        Choose the ride for which you wish to see the bookings and click on the "Bookings" link.
                                        To make sure you choose the right ride, all the rides information is displayed.
                                        Under this information, the people who have booked your ride are listed also with their booking status.
                                        If you wish to check the accounts, just click on their avatars (pictures).

                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        One more way how to see people who have booked your ride and where you can accept or reject them is on "Booking" page on the top next to the page with "Rides". 
                                        Here you can see the list of all people who booked your ride.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>Can I reject someone who booked my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>If for whatever reason you do not want to ride with a particular person, you can reject the booking offer.</p>

                                    <h4>Can I reject someone even after I accepted his or her booking request?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        You are allowed to change your opinion about the people who are going to drive with you anytime.
                                        So even if you had accepted someone's booking offer previously, you can still cancel this booking of your ride. 
                                        Just open the page "Bookings" next to the "Rides" page on the top of the page.
                                        Here you can see "Cancel" button next to the person who you accepted. 
                                        After clicking on it, the passenger's bookings will be cancelled.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Another way on how to cancel an already accepted booking is to open your personal profile page and then open "My Rides" section.
                                        Here click on "Bookings" link in the ride you want to see.
                                        Next to each person on the page there are options.
                                        If someone is accepted there you can also see "Cancel" button next to it. 
                                        After clicking on it, the passenger's bookings will be cancelled.
                                    </p>

                                    <h4>How to contact people who are taking my ride?</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        At present time, the only way to directly contact users who booked your ride, is to reply on the automatically sent booking message.
                                        It means you have to open the "messages" which are between your name and notification bell on the top of the page.
                                        Here you see the message from the person who booked your ride which was automatically sent to you.
                                        At the end of the message, there is the button "Reply".
                                        After you click on it, the passenger's name will appear as the person who you are going to send the message to.
                                        Now you can write what you want and just click on "send" button.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
