                            <h4>What does it mean to make a booking?</h4>
                            <p>
                                If you want to join a ride with someone from one place to the other on exact date, you can make a booking of his or her ride.
                                After the driver accepts your request, you can drive together to your destination.

                            </p>

                            <h4>How much does it cost to take a ride?</h4>
                            <p>Our application is free of charge.
                               It means you will not be charged anything as well as no one will pay you for anything.</p>

                            <h4>How to make a booking?</h4>
                            <p>
                                You need to be logged in to book a ride.
                                Go to the page with "Rides" where you can find the specific ride for you.
                                After you have one, click on the  "Details" link in the end of the line where is the ride.
                                You will see the page with all details and the driver.
                                On the right side, there is a button for booking  the ride.
                                After you click on it, you will see your list of bookings with the booking status. 
                                Now you have to wait until the driver accepts or rejects your request.
                                In case you have already booked the ride the button for booking it will not allow you to book it once again 
                                and the system will not allow you to book your own ride.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                You can also open your personal profile page and choose "My bookings" option on your left. 
                                Here you can see a button "Book a Ride" which will redirect you to the page with all rides. 
                                Here continue as mentioned above.
                            </p>

                            <h4>Why is the map in details of specific ride not showing the route?</h4>
                            <p>
                                In case the driver has misspelt the departure location or the destionation, the map cannot identify where it is starting or ending.
                                If the map does not know the exact points, then it cannot also calculate how long the journey will take. 
                            </p>

                            <h4>Where can I see my bookings?</h4>
                            <p>
                                To see your bookings you need to be logged in.
                                Open your personal profile page and choose My bookings section. 
                                Here you can see the list of all your bookings with their corresponding status.
                            </p>

                            <h4>What does the booking status mean?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Our system has exactly 4 different booking status.
                                "Pending" means that the driver has not accepted or rejected your booking.
                                "Accepted" means that the driver accepted your booking.
                                "Rejected" means that the driver does not wish to drive with you.
                                "Cancelled" means that even if you were accepted, the driver changed his mind and decided to cancel the booking request.
                                Alternatively, something might have happened and the driver eventually decided to cancel your acceptance
                                or you can also be the one who eventually decides   not to take the ride with the driver and cancels the booking.

                            </p>

                            <h4>Is it possible to cancel my booking?</h4>
                            <p>
                                You can always cancel the booking in case you cannot join the ride. 
                                You can do so on your own profile page in "My Bookings" section. 
                                There you can find the "Cancel" button next to the booking you wish to cancel. 
                                Make sure you are cancelling the right booking.
                            </p>

                            <h4>Is it possible to cancel the booking even after the driver has confirmed it?</h4>
                            <p>You can always cancel the booking if you cannot join the ride. 
                                To find more information how to cancel it, check the previous question "Is it possible to cancel my booking?"</p>

                            <h4>How do I know if my booking has been accepted by the driver?</h4>
                            <p>You can see it under the notification bell or under "My bookings" on your personal profile page. 
                            Each of these pages displays the status of your bookings.</p>

                            <h4>How to contact a driver who accepted my booking?</h4>
                            <p>
                                To contact the driver, open the "details" page of the ride and there you can see the area with "Send me a message". 
                                This message is sent to the driver. 
                                To find out more about  the Messages, check the Messages section in questions for "everyone" using the App.
                            </p>

                            <h4>What is the search function in bookings for?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The search function on pages with bookings is for searching the bookings with the same status.
                                It means, when you want to see all Accepted bookings for example, you can just type "Accepted" into the search field and you will see all of them.
                                By this way you can for example find out which driver is rejecting you or cancelling your bookings more often than others.
                            </p>
